Package: XenoMix
Title: Cross-Species Contamination Detection and Quantification for Infinium Methylation Arrays
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Nima", "Esmaeelpour", , "nima.esmaeelpour@dkfz.de", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Quantifies murine DNA contamination in human Infinium Methylation EPIC arrays by exploiting species-specific signal discordance. Leveraging Infinium Type I probe biochemistry, the algorithm identifies inter-species informative probes where single-base extension color channels differ between human and mouse genomes even after bisulfite conversion. While the technical capacity for cross-species detection was initially noted by Zhou et al. (2022) for human DNA on mouse-specific arrays, this package provides the first formalized framework and background-correction logic to accurately estimate the reciprocal case of host contamination in human-targeted xenograft samples. Validation against in-house ground-truth mixtures and 227 publicly available datasets from the Gene Expression Omnibus demonstrates high estimation accuracy ($R^2 = 0.991$), providing a robust quality-control metric for preclinical xenograft epigenomics.
